                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d134">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.569/20</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Netherland Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">De Graeff</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-08-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1924</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: I beg to acknowledge the receipt
                    of your note dated August 6, 1924, in which you inquire whether it will be <pb
                        facs="0321" n="207" xml:id="pg_207"/> possible that the so-called liquor
                    treaty between the United States and the Netherlands be put in force from the
                    date of the signature of the treaty without awaiting its ratification, so that
                    the American authorities would be entitled from the date of signature to board
                    and search Netherlands ships outside of the three mile limit and Netherlands
                    ships would be entitled to carry alcoholic beverages under seal within that
                    limit from the same date.</p>
                <p>By way of response I am obliged to inform you that this Government finds itself
                    unable to give application to the treaty prior to the exchange of ratifications
                    and proclamation thereof.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles E. Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
